(1. Introduction) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Lotus is characterized by three bomb sites, rotating doors, and short transition corridors.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(These properties amplify the value of information and make delayed pivots highly sensitive to) Tj
0 -15 Td
(utility usage. While many public guides describe site executes in isolation, fewer frameworks) Tj
0 -15 Td
(offer a full-cycle method that links opening pressure, neutral reset, and second-wave) Tj
0 -15 Td
(commitment. This paper treats rotation as a state machine and argues that triple-smoke lineups) Tj
0 -15 Td
(can stabilize decision quality when supported by explicit timing rules.) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
(2. Map-State Representation) Tj
0 -15 Td
(We define each mid-round state as S = \(C, U, I, T\), where C denotes controlled sectors, U) Tj
0 -15 Td
(denotes remaining smoke charges and support utility, I denotes confirmed enemy information, and) Tj
0 -15 Td
(T denotes round time bucket. A pivot is recommended only when two conditions are satisfied:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(first, at least one defensive anchor is probabilistically displaced by pressure utility; second,) Tj
0 -15 Td
(the expected corridor risk on the target path remains below a preset threshold derived from) Tj
0 -15 Td
(recent engagement logs.) Tj
0 -15 Td
