(3. Triple-Smoke Rotation Protocol) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The proposed protocol uses three role assignments: Initiator-Smoke, Anchor-Smoke, and Delay-) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Smoke. Phase A applies contact pressure and a low-cost fake marker. Phase B enforces an eight-) Tj
0 -15 Td
(to-twelve-second information window in which no hard commit occurs unless a high-confidence pick) Tj
0 -15 Td
(is achieved. Phase C triggers rotation and executes staggered smoke drops: entry choke cover at) Tj
0 -15 Td
(t0, anti-retake lane denial at t0 plus 2 seconds, and late-site isolation at t0 plus 6 seconds.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The temporal spacing reduces overlap waste and preserves one survivability layer for post-plant.) Tj
0 -15 Td
() Tj
0 -15 Td
